21/08/2005
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- UN special envoy Kai Eide called on Friday (19 August) for launching the process of repatriating displaced persons in Kosovo as soon as possible.
Speaking after his meeting with Kosovo Returns Minister Slavisa Petkovic, he said the repatriation process was not simply a technical issue but was related to security, the rule of law and healthcare.
He called for dialogue between Pristina and Belgrade aimed at achieving a speedy resolution of the issues.
After spending five days in Kosovo, Eide visits Belgrade on Monday.
(Tanjug - 20/08/05;
B92 - 19/08/05)
